{"id": "9ec2959d-5dbe-4c63-98b7-d69b3667192a", "url": "http://ipt.iobis.org/obiscanada/resource?r=dal_laurent2011", "archive": "https://ipt.iobis.org/obiscanada/archive.do?r=dal_laurent2011", "published": "2026-02-11T22:02:05.000Z", "created": null, "updated": "2026-02-11T22:11:43.107Z", "core": "occurrence", "extensions": [], "statistics": {"Event": 0, "absence": 0, "dropped": 0, "Occurrence": 1149, "DNADerivedData": 0, "MeasurementOrFact": 0}, "extent": "POLYGON((-64.3067 44.28466,-64.2 44.28466,-64.2 44.3575,-64.3067 44.3575,-64.3067 44.28466))", "title": "Dalhousie University: Drift net plankton samples collected in Lunenburg Bay, 2005-2006", "citation": "Laurent, Arnaud. (2013).  Drift net plankton samples collected in Lunenburg Bay, 2005-2006. Version 1 In OBIS Canada Digital Collections. Bedford Institute of Oceanography, Dartmouth, NS, Canada. Published by OBIS, Digital http://www.iobis.org/. Accessed on \u2013INSERT DATE", "citation_id": "http://iobis.org/mapper/?resource_id=2805", "abstract": "\n            <p>This resource contains plankton species distribution records extracted from the Fisheries and Oceans Canada BioChem database for the 'Dal thesis - Arnaud Laurent - Lunenburg Bay' series of records. These distribution records were collected as part of a university PhD thesis project designed to investigate variability in plankton dynamics found in Lunenburg Bay, an inlet on the Atlantic coast of Nova Scotia,Canada (Lunenburg Bay Project)\nThis OBIS resource contains a subset of the archived database records - at this time only abundance information has been released.</p>\n        ", "intellectualrights": "This work is licensed under a  Creative Commons Attribution (CC-BY 4.0) License", "feed": {"id": "6ae5ad4f-2a01-43bd-9fb4-cc9c7f38f105", "url": "http://ipt.vliz.be/obiscanada/rss.do"}, "institutes": [{"name": "OBIS Canada", "oceanexpert_id": 19633, "oceanexpert_parent_id": 19196}], "contacts": [{"role": null, "type": "creator", "givenname": "Arnaud",